The Western Cape Health Department has confirmed two children have died after allegedly ingesting poisonous food and not three as previously reported. CAPE TOWN - The Western Cape Health Department has confirmed two children have died after allegedly ingesting poisonous food - and not three as previously reported.The incident occurred at the weekend.The deceased were among three adults and five children who suffered severe diarrhoea after apparently eating contaminated meat.Spokesperson for the Health MEC Zimkitha Mquteni says three other children are in a serious but stable condition at the Red Cross War Memorial children s hospital. We can confirm that one female patient has been discharged from our facility in the Mitchells Plain Hospital. The male patient is still in a critical condition at Groote Schuur Hospital. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)